flavorText: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.
A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.
The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.
To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.
It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.
It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.
It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.
It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.
It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.
They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokémon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokémon.
This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It's famous for being a hard worker.
This Pokémon was not originally found in Alola. Human actions caused a surge in their numbers, and they went feral. They're prideful and crafty.
This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.
While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.
A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.
With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.
Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.
As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.
It's both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.

After a 10-hour struggle, a fisherman was able to pull one up and confirm its existence.
Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.
Roughly 20 years ago, it was artificially created, utilizing the latest technology of the time.

Feared for its wrath and the curses it spreads, this Pokémon will also, on a whim, cast spells that help people.

It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.
It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.
Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.
It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.
It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.
Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They're jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

With a voice like a human child's, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.
Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.
Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.
It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.
It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.
